description:
&lt;p&gt;Whittington Health Trust are seeking experienced and committed Band 6 Midwives to join the UCLH Bank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for enthusiastic Midwives to join the highly motivated midwifery team, working in a modern and well equipped facility, this is an excellent opportunity for those wishing to further develop their clinical skills as well as gain valuable experience working in all areas of the maternity service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a midwife who would like to be a part of our future and can meet this challenge we welcome your interest in a post with us – please apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required skills &amp; experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Midwife&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NMC Registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experienced working in an NHS Maternity Unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 6 month post registration experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bank Nurses are invaluable to us and in return for their dedication and commitment, we offer the following benefits:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working hours and weekly payroll services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A designated onsite co-ordinator to offer support and arrange ward visits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated recruitment team to ensure you can work as quickly as possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bookings team that are open 365 days a year to ensure you work when and wherever you want to&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a minimum 6 months NHS experience and you are looking to further your career in a hospital that has cutting edge technology, please apply online.&lt;/p&gt;
